01:10:40,459 --> 01:10:41,575
can have a brighter future--

1317
01:10:41,670 --> 01:10:43,503
a future of economic growth,

1318
01:10:43,629 --> 01:10:44,791
freedom, and happiness.

1319
01:10:44,880 --> 01:10:46,794
On tonight's show,

1320
01:10:46,883 --> 01:10:49,958
a visionary and true patriot:

1321
01:10:50,053 --> 01:10:54,004
the CEO of Omnicorp,
Raymond Sellars.

1322
01:10:54,140 --> 01:10:55,849
(applause)

1323
01:10:55,975 --> 01:10:56,842
- Hello, Pat.
- Raymond.

1324
01:10:56,977 --> 01:10:58,308
Thanks for having me.

1325
01:10:58,436 --> 01:11:01,022
You must be doing a
victory lap about now.

1326
01:11:01,147 --> 01:11:03,140
- Well...
- Two weeks ago,

1327
01:11:03,232 --> 01:11:05,647
Omni's stock went
through the roof,

1328
01:11:05,735 --> 01:11:08,149
and the Senate
has finally agreed

1329
01:11:08,237 --> 01:11:10,481
to vote on the repeal
of the Dreyfus Act.

1330
01:11:10,615 --> 01:11:13,451
Well, look, I mean,
the tide is definitely turning.

1331
01:11:13,535 --> 01:11:15,495
I, I just feel certain
that, soon,

1332
01:11:15,580 --> 01:11:16,991
we'll be keeping
all Americans safe.

1333
01:11:17,080 --> 01:11:18,163
I certainly
hope so,

1334
01:11:18,248 --> 01:11:20,333
but I think
our next guest will have

1335
01:11:20,418 --> 01:11:21,453
a different point of view.

1336
01:11:21,543 --> 01:11:22,660
SELLARS:
Mm-hmm.

1337
01:11:22,753 --> 01:11:24,336
Hubert Dreyfus.

1338
01:11:24,421 --> 01:11:26,460
Senator, thank you
for joining us.

1339
01:11:26,548 --> 01:11:27,881
Hello, Pat. Mr. Sellars.

1340
01:11:28,008 --> 01:11:30,878
Senator, do you know
what this is?

1341
01:11:31,011 --> 01:11:33,551
The American public is divided

1342
01:11:33,681 --> 01:11:35,172
on the Dreyfus Act.

1343
01:11:35,349 --> 01:11:40,178
Our polls at NovakEIement.com
are tight at 50-50.

1344
01:11:40,312 --> 01:11:44,185
There is no doubt Omnicorp
created a sensation,

1345
01:11:44,317 --> 01:11:47,813
but this bill is not
about Alex Murphy.

1346
01:11:47,903 --> 01:11:50,694
It's about whether America
is willing to give robots

1347
01:11:50,781 --> 01:11:51,864
the authority
over human lives.

1348
01:11:51,992 --> 01:11:54,486
No, no, no, no,
look, look, look.

1349
01:11:54,577 --> 01:11:57,163
This, uh, sea change
we're witnessing--

1350
01:11:57,247 --> 01:12:00,117
and it is a sea change-- shows
that Americans don't really care

1351
01:12:00,208 --> 01:12:02,919
if our law enforcement systems
are manned or unmanned.

1352
01:12:03,044 --> 01:12:04,912
What they care about
is efficiency

1353
01:12:05,046 --> 01:12:06,333
and they care about safety.

1354
01:12:06,422 --> 01:12:07,880
You're clouding
the issue.

1355
01:12:08,008 --> 01:12:10,719
This is clearly an attempt
to sway public opinion

1356
01:12:10,802 --> 01:12:13,341
-with a marketing stunt.
- No, what's clear is

1357
01:12:13,429 --> 01:12:15,173
that with just one system
in place,

1358
01:12:15,266 --> 01:12:16,723
We've cut crime by 80%.

1359
01:12:16,808 --> 01:12:19,347
Just imagine if we put,
I don't know,

1360
01:12:19,435 --> 01:12:20,724
let's say
a hundred systems in place.

1361
01:12:20,813 --> 01:12:23,728
And then I want you
to ask yourself,

1362
01:12:23,815 --> 01:12:25,354
why are you holding us back?

1363
01:12:25,443 --> 01:12:26,558
- Is that your plan?
- Thank you, Senator.

1364
01:12:26,693 --> 01:12:28,561
- And thank you, Raymond.
- Thank you, Pat.

1365
01:12:28,654 --> 01:12:31,945
Well, there you have it.

1366
01:12:32,073 --> 01:12:33,942
Who could argue with that?

1367
01:12:34,076 --> 01:12:36,695
Which begs the question:

1368
01:12:36,828 --> 01:12:38,913
has the U.S. Senate

1369
01:12:38,998 --> 01:12:42,494
become pro-crime?

1370
01:12:45,422 --> 01:12:47,414
(phone ringing)

1371
01:12:49,842 --> 01:12:50,753
(phone rings, then beeps on)

1372
01:12:50,885 --> 01:12:52,423
Yeah, hi.

1373
01:12:52,512 --> 01:12:54,255
No, no, $5,000.

1374
01:12:54,347 --> 01:12:55,931
Yeah, call me tomorrow.

1375
01:12:56,058 --> 01:12:58,769
Hey, guys.

1376
01:12:58,894 --> 01:13:01,605
Vallon's waiting
for you inside.

1377
01:13:01,730 --> 01:13:03,267
What, you too busy
to walk us in?

1378
01:13:03,398 --> 01:13:04,855
- I'm out here making money.
- Yeah, no, I know.

1379
01:13:04,983 --> 01:13:06,098
VALLON:
Where are my trip wires?

1380
01:13:06,235 --> 01:13:07,772
I gotta do this myself?

1381
01:13:07,861 --> 01:13:09,227
What took you so long?

1382
01:13:09,321 --> 01:13:10,437
DANIELS: What the hell
is all this shit?

1383
01:13:10,572 --> 01:13:11,564
I can't move any product

1384
01:13:11,657 --> 01:13:14,402
with this thing on the streets.

1385
01:13:14,493 --> 01:13:15,825
What are you doing
to protect me?

1386
01:13:15,953 --> 01:13:17,992
Relax, the guy's
a walking zombie.

1387
01:13:18,121 --> 01:13:19,454
Tell me your phones are off.

1388
01:13:19,582 --> 01:13:20,448
He's not going after you.

1389
01:13:20,583 --> 01:13:21,950
We covered our tracks.

1390
01:13:22,043 --> 01:13:24,412
He can't manufacture evidence
out of thin air.

1391
01:13:24,503 --> 01:13:26,462
If he does, I'm ready for him.

1392
01:13:26,589 --> 01:13:28,958
(thudding, whirring)

1393
01:13:34,889 --> 01:13:36,881
Well?

1394
01:13:39,894 --> 01:13:41,260
I've been getting calls.

1395
01:13:41,354 --> 01:13:43,188
From whom?

1396
01:13:43,314 --> 01:13:44,772
Well, Clara.

1397
01:13:44,858 --> 01:13:46,645
You need to let her
see her husband.

1398
01:13:46,734 --> 01:13:48,978
She has rights.

1399
01:13:49,112 --> 01:13:50,320
That's not your decision.

1400
01:13:50,405 --> 01:13:52,272
That's Legal's call.

1401
01:13:52,365 --> 01:13:54,359
Yeah, but it's only
a question of time

1402
01:13:54,493 --> 01:13:56,862
before she turns up
on television.

1403
01:13:56,995 --> 01:13:58,989
Well, she can try.

1404
01:13:59,081 --> 01:14:01,871
I'll issue a gag order before
I let her see her husband.

1405
01:14:03,419 --> 01:14:05,535
- I'd hop to it.
- CLARA (voice-over): Alex.

1406
01:14:05,670 --> 01:14:08,382
Alex, Alex!

1407
01:14:09,508 --> 01:14:11,468
Alex.

1408
01:14:11,552 --> 01:14:13,385
You need to come home.

1409
01:14:13,513 --> 01:14:15,050
Clara, please stand aside.

1410
01:14:15,180 --> 01:14:17,299
- You need to speak to your son.
- Right now,

1411
01:14:17,392 --> 01:14:18,679
I see three crimes in progress.

1412
01:14:18,809 --> 01:14:20,346
- My objective...
- Alex, listen to me.

1413
01:14:20,435 --> 01:14:22,850
I know you're in there.

1414
01:14:24,899 --> 01:14:27,064
David won't show
his face at school.

1415
01:14:27,985 --> 01:14:29,853
He's having nightmares.

1416
01:14:29,987 --> 01:14:32,322
He's falling apart.

1417
01:14:32,407 --> 01:14:34,024
I'm falling apart.

1418
01:14:34,116 --> 01:14:35,233
(gasping)

1419
01:14:35,368 --> 01:14:38,204
Please.

1420
01:14:38,329 --> 01:14:40,539
I can't do this on my own.

1421
01:14:40,666 --> 01:14:41,827
He's been scared

1422
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:44,586
ever since that night.

1423
01:14:48,799 --> 01:14:50,542
-(clamoring)
- Come on, brother...!

1424
01:14:53,178 --> 01:14:55,047
LIZ (voice-over): What do you
think she's gonna do?

1425
01:14:55,181 --> 01:14:58,142
Hm. What's he gonna do?

1426
01:15:07,192 --> 01:15:09,607
(crowd clamoring)

1427
01:15:18,996 --> 01:15:20,989
Are you okay? David...?

1428
01:15:26,254 --> 01:15:28,121
(car horn honks)

1429
01:15:28,255 --> 01:15:31,706
(tires screech)

1430
01:15:40,602 --> 01:15:44,224
(tires screeching,
engine roaring)

1431
01:15:44,314 --> 01:15:46,934
KIM (voice-over): He's supposed
to be watching this.

1432
01:15:47,067 --> 01:15:50,769
Instead he's accessing
images of Clara and David

1433
01:15:50,863 --> 01:15:54,234
arriving at school,
over and over again.

1434
01:15:54,324 --> 01:15:56,909
Somehow he's overriding

1435
01:15:57,034 --> 01:15:59,278
the system's priorities.

1436
01:16:08,381 --> 01:16:10,294
KIM (voice-over):
Want me to shut him down?

1437
01:16:10,424 --> 01:16:11,289
NORTON (voice-over):
No.

1438
01:16:11,425 --> 01:16:14,011
Not yet.

1439
01:16:14,137 --> 01:16:16,130
I want to see what happens.

1440
01:16:27,358 --> 01:16:30,353
♪♪

1441
01:16:35,824 --> 01:16:38,068
KIM:
What's he doing at his house?

1442
01:16:39,954 --> 01:16:41,823
Look, he's
disobeying protocol.

1443
01:16:41,957 --> 01:16:43,368
You have to
shut him down.

1444
01:16:43,499 --> 01:16:46,701
As far as I can tell,
he's still doing his job.

1445
01:16:53,468 --> 01:16:56,463
♪♪

1446
01:17:05,606 --> 01:17:08,020
(deep whirring, blipping)

1447
01:17:12,780 --> 01:17:14,489
(car alarm blaring)

1448
01:17:25,376 --> 01:17:28,668
(whirring, footsteps thudding)

1449
01:17:45,940 --> 01:17:47,682
Adrian, give me an image

1450
01:17:47,774 --> 01:17:49,733
of his brain.

1451
01:17:49,818 --> 01:17:53,690
He's undoing what
we did to him.

1452
01:17:53,780 --> 01:17:56,114
His dopamine levels are
coming back to normal.

1453
01:17:56,242 --> 01:17:58,656
How is that
even possible?

1454
01:18:00,079 --> 01:18:02,698
I haven't the faintest idea.

1455
01:18:02,789 --> 01:18:04,281
NORTON (over radio):
Alex.

1456
01:18:15,678 --> 01:18:16,884
(whirring)

1457
01:18:21,600 --> 01:18:23,890
(engine roaring)

1458
01:18:30,610 --> 01:18:33,275
Alex, please return
to the station.

1459
01:18:33,405 --> 01:18:36,571
I want to run some tests.

1460
01:18:36,658 --> 01:18:38,402
Well, this should
be interesting.

1461
01:18:38,494 --> 01:18:40,612
(engine roaring)

1462
01:18:54,718 --> 01:18:56,461
ALEX (recorded):
And your phone on the table!

1463
01:18:56,595 --> 01:18:58,429
We're not cops, all right?
We work for Antoine Vallon.

1464
01:18:58,514 --> 01:18:59,801
- What?
- Whoa!

1465
01:18:59,890 --> 01:19:01,975
What'd you say?

1466
01:19:02,060 --> 01:19:04,019
We work for Antoine Vallon.

1467
01:19:13,947 --> 01:19:16,692
(engine roaring)

1468
01:19:21,537 --> 01:19:25,206
(dog barking in distance)

1469
01:19:29,337 --> 01:19:30,204
(groans)

1470
01:19:30,339 --> 01:19:32,173
(screaming)

1471
01:19:32,257 --> 01:19:33,999
My hand, man!

1472
01:19:34,133 --> 01:19:35,216
- Where's Antoine Vallon?
- You broke

1473
01:19:35,344 --> 01:19:36,631
my hand, man!

1474
01:19:36,720 --> 01:19:39,340
I know you remember me, Jerry.

1475
01:19:39,431 --> 01:19:42,141
-(bones crackling)
-(screaming)

1476
01:19:42,266 --> 01:19:43,805
Where's Vallon?

1477
01:19:43,894 --> 01:19:45,351
JERRY: Aah!
Wait, wait, man, wait, man!

1478
01:19:45,437 --> 01:19:46,473
If I tell you where Vallon is,

1479
01:19:46,563 --> 01:19:48,352
he'll kill my wife and kid, man.

1480
01:19:48,483 --> 01:19:49,973
Your wife left you

1481
01:19:50,066 --> 01:19:53,029
in 2019 after filing charges
for domestic abuse,

1482
01:19:53,113 --> 01:19:55,196
and you don't have a kid.

1483
01:19:55,280 --> 01:19:56,647
But I do.

1484
01:19:56,741 --> 01:19:58,199
(screams, bones crackle)

1485
01:19:58,284 --> 01:19:59,524
I'm not asking again!

1486
01:19:59,659 --> 01:20:00,571
Look, I swear, man,

1487
01:20:00,703 --> 01:20:01,819
I don't know
where Vallon is, okay?

1488
01:20:01,912 --> 01:20:03,905
The only guy I talk to is
his driver Marcus.

1489
01:20:04,039 --> 01:20:05,371
That's it, man, that's it!

1490
01:20:05,457 --> 01:20:07,872
Does he have a phone number?

1491
01:20:17,887 --> 01:20:20,723
(engine roaring)

1492
01:20:23,601 --> 01:20:24,809
We have a problem.

1493
01:20:24,895 --> 01:20:26,979
Alex is breaking protocol.

1494
01:20:27,105 --> 01:20:28,267
What's he doing?

1495
01:20:28,398 --> 01:20:30,768
He's off solving
his own murder.

1496
01:20:30,901 --> 01:20:33,692
Oh, that is genius.

1497
01:20:33,779 --> 01:20:35,772
Why didn't I think of that?

1498
01:20:42,454 --> 01:20:44,367
VALLON (voice-over):
How long till he gets here?

1499
01:20:44,456 --> 01:20:46,620
All right.

1500
01:20:46,750 --> 01:20:48,413
Johnny, you stay
on these monitors.

1501
01:20:48,502 --> 01:20:51,087
What happened?

1502
01:20:51,172 --> 01:20:54,588
Some idiot used
an unencrypted phone.

1503
01:20:54,716 --> 01:20:57,336
Shit.

1504
01:21:04,643 --> 01:21:06,478
VALLON:
All right, everyone, listen up!

1505
01:21:06,604 --> 01:21:07,811
He's coming.

1506
01:21:07,940 --> 01:21:12,142
He leaves alive, you don't.

1507
01:21:12,277 --> 01:21:13,564
MAN:
How do we stop him?

1508
01:21:15,071 --> 01:21:16,940
.50-caliber and above.

1509
01:21:17,032 --> 01:21:18,489
Aim for the head.

1510
01:21:28,292 --> 01:21:30,081
(beep)

1511
01:21:30,170 --> 01:21:31,412
This one's set!

1512
01:21:31,505 --> 01:21:32,961
Go! Go!

1513
01:21:33,090 --> 01:21:34,126
(beeping)

1514
01:21:34,216 --> 01:21:35,207
(man yells in distance)

1515
01:21:36,218 --> 01:21:37,505
Come on. Come on!

1516
01:21:39,847 --> 01:21:40,838
Ready to go!

1517
01:21:41,890 --> 01:21:43,803
They're all set.

1518
01:21:43,934 --> 01:21:45,347
(power whirrs off)

1519
01:21:47,855 --> 01:21:48,846
(switch clicks)

1520
01:21:52,860 --> 01:21:54,854
(guns cocking)

1521
01:21:56,279 --> 01:21:58,991
(motorcycle engine
decelerates)

1522
01:21:59,117 --> 01:22:00,734
(engine idling)

1523
01:22:00,826 --> 01:22:02,695
(engine revving)

1524
01:22:17,845 --> 01:22:20,258
♪♪

1525
01:22:30,900 --> 01:22:32,687
(grunts)

1526
01:22:46,291 --> 01:22:49,366
♪♪

1527
01:22:59,471 --> 01:23:02,545
♪♪

1528
01:23:10,356 --> 01:23:12,566
Finish it!

1529
01:23:18,949 --> 01:23:19,940
(RoboCop groans)

1530
01:23:22,829 --> 01:23:24,365
(whirring)

1531
01:23:26,415 --> 01:23:28,124
Freak! Die!

1532
01:23:37,551 --> 01:23:38,713
(groans)

1533
01:23:41,348 --> 01:23:43,556
(whirring, footsteps thudding)

1534
01:23:50,690 --> 01:23:52,682
(whirring, thudding)

1535
01:24:01,868 --> 01:24:03,861
(blipping, whirring)

1536
01:24:09,377 --> 01:24:11,368
♪♪

1537
01:24:17,175 --> 01:24:18,838
Watch out.

1538
01:24:18,969 --> 01:24:20,176
Need me to call a doctor?

1539
01:24:20,303 --> 01:24:22,638
Come on, Jack.
You're gonna like this.

1540
01:24:24,391 --> 01:24:26,350
What's going on?
What the hell you doing here?

1541
01:24:26,476 --> 01:24:27,809
Y'all gonna play
good cop, bad cop?

1542
01:24:27,937 --> 01:24:29,553
Nah, Daniels,
bad cop, RoboCop.

1543
01:24:32,274 --> 01:24:33,983
ROBOCOP:
I've recovered 26 guns

1544
01:24:34,067 --> 01:24:35,150
from Vallon's warehouse.

1545
01:24:35,236 --> 01:24:36,477
13 serial numbers

1546
01:24:36,570 --> 01:24:38,154
match weapons missing
from Evidence,

1547
01:24:38,239 --> 01:24:39,479
and I got your prints
all over them.

1548
01:24:39,573 --> 01:24:41,316
This is bullshit.

1549
01:24:41,409 --> 01:24:42,445
I also have

1550
01:24:42,576 --> 01:24:44,535
CCTV footage of you and Vallon

1551
01:24:44,662 --> 01:24:45,995
the same day he
tried to kill me.

1552
01:24:46,080 --> 01:24:47,663
VALLON:
So put him on the payroll.

1553
01:24:47,790 --> 01:24:49,533
- Why we talking about this?
- DANIELS: It won't work.

1554
01:24:49,667 --> 01:24:51,661
Now that his partner got hit,
he's never gonna let it go.

1555
01:24:51,753 --> 01:24:53,336
- What is that?
- Lewis's hospital.

1556
01:24:53,462 --> 01:24:54,954
Murphy's dropping by
this afternoon.

1557
01:24:55,131 --> 01:24:56,498
If I kill a cop, I'm looking
over my shoulder.

1558
01:24:56,591 --> 01:24:57,831
I kill a cop,
I'm looking over...

1559
01:24:57,925 --> 01:24:59,292
LEWIS:
You know what they do to cops

1560
01:24:59,386 --> 01:25:01,345
in prison, man?
Being locked up

1561
01:25:01,430 --> 01:25:02,887
with the same dudes
you put in there?

1562
01:25:03,014 --> 01:25:04,802
VALLON: I kill a cop,
I'm looking over my shoulder

1563
01:25:04,891 --> 01:25:05,677
the rest of my life.

1564
01:25:05,767 --> 01:25:06,724
If I kill a cop...

1565
01:25:06,851 --> 01:25:08,513
How long you think
before he gives you up?

1566
01:25:08,602 --> 01:25:10,312
(people screaming)

1567
01:25:11,189 --> 01:25:12,807
Don't shoot me.

1568
01:25:12,899 --> 01:25:15,735
Okay?

1569
01:25:15,819 --> 01:25:18,234
I swear to Christ, it was Dean.

1570
01:25:18,363 --> 01:25:19,901
She helped pull those guns.

1571
01:25:19,990 --> 01:25:22,985
Just don't shoot me.

1572
01:25:23,077 --> 01:25:24,786
Thank you
for your cooperation.

1573
01:25:25,995 --> 01:25:27,158
(Lake groaning)

1574
01:25:27,247 --> 01:25:28,956
You can cuff him now, Jack.

1575
01:25:37,884 --> 01:25:40,344
Now, I know why
we couldn't get an arrest.

1576
01:25:40,428 --> 01:25:43,219
'Cause Vallon was protected
from up on high.

1577
01:25:43,348 --> 01:25:45,557
Alex, I can explain.

1578
01:25:45,683 --> 01:25:46,924
You tipped him off today.

1579
01:25:47,059 --> 01:25:48,142
Come on, man.
Don't do this.

1580
01:25:48,269 --> 01:25:50,011
You tried to kill me twice.

1581
01:25:50,104 --> 01:25:52,223
I trusted you,

1582
01:25:52,315 --> 01:25:53,772
and you destroyed my family.

1583
01:25:53,899 --> 01:25:56,234
Confess.

1584
01:25:56,319 --> 01:25:58,232
Now, in front of everyone.

1585
01:25:58,363 --> 01:25:59,229
Confess!

1586
01:25:59,364 --> 01:26:00,982
(power whirrs off)

1587
01:26:09,124 --> 01:26:10,035
What happened?

1588
01:26:10,166 --> 01:26:11,249
MATTOX (over radio):
Tin Man is down.

1589
01:26:11,377 --> 01:26:12,412
Had to be done.

1590
01:26:12,502 --> 01:26:13,539
Why?

1591
01:26:13,629 --> 01:26:14,961
Product shot a corrupt cop.

1592
01:26:15,088 --> 01:26:16,546
Two more seconds,
the chief's brains

1593
01:26:16,632 --> 01:26:19,218
would've been splattered
across the 6:00 News.

1594
01:26:19,301 --> 01:26:21,590
- We got anything on her?
- Well, she's, uh,

1595
01:26:21,678 --> 01:26:23,296
the Chief of the Detroit
Police Department.

1596
01:26:23,430 --> 01:26:25,799
What do you think?

1597
01:26:28,519 --> 01:26:30,762
You know what?

1598
01:26:30,896 --> 01:26:34,474
This might actually tip
this thing right into the net.

1599
01:26:41,282 --> 01:26:44,118
NOVAK: Alex, I don't know
if you can hear me,

1600
01:26:44,201 --> 01:26:48,120
but tonight,
you uncovered a nest of vipers

1601
01:26:48,248 --> 01:26:50,287
inside the Detroit
Police Department.

1602
01:26:50,375 --> 01:26:52,915
And in so doing, you shed light

1603
01:26:53,003 --> 01:26:55,747
on an invaluable truth.

1604
01:26:55,838 --> 01:26:57,251
Even the police,

1605
01:26:57,340 --> 01:26:58,957
the men and women

1606
01:26:59,050 --> 01:27:01,967
who swore to keep us safe,

1607
01:27:02,095 --> 01:27:04,179
they can be bribed.

1608
01:27:04,264 --> 01:27:06,884
They... can be bought.

1609
01:27:08,518 --> 01:27:10,808
Machines, however,

1610
01:27:10,938 --> 01:27:13,307
are corruption-free.

1611
01:27:13,399 --> 01:27:16,190
Americans could be living
in a country

1612
01:27:16,319 --> 01:27:19,644
where law enforcement
is not only efficient,

1613
01:27:19,738 --> 01:27:22,653
but incorruptible.

1614
01:27:22,741 --> 01:27:24,700
Thank you, Alex,
for all you've done,

1615
01:27:24,827 --> 01:27:26,866
and for all that you are.

1616
01:27:26,995 --> 01:27:30,321
Detective Murphy is currently
in critical condition.

1617
01:27:30,499 --> 01:27:33,163
Our doctors are
working ceaselessly

1618
01:27:33,252 --> 01:27:36,167
but, at this time, it is
unclear if he will survive.

1619
01:27:36,296 --> 01:27:37,881
(reporters clamoring)

1620
01:27:38,007 --> 01:27:39,875
KELLY: Ms. Kline,
how do you think the attempt

1621
01:27:40,009 --> 01:27:41,968
on Detective
Alex Murphy's life

1622
01:27:42,053 --> 01:27:44,343
will affect tomorrow's vote
for the Dreyfus Act?

1623
01:27:44,431 --> 01:27:46,218
LIZ: At this time,
Omnicorp's sole concern

1624
01:27:46,349 --> 01:27:48,810
is the full recovery
of Detective Murphy.

1625
01:27:48,893 --> 01:27:51,182
NOVAK: How many times
does Detective Murphy

1626
01:27:51,354 --> 01:27:54,190
have to give his life
for his country?

1627
01:27:54,315 --> 01:27:57,858
I sincerely hope

1628
01:27:57,987 --> 01:27:59,854
the Senate makes
the right vote tomorrow,

1629
01:27:59,946 --> 01:28:01,689
so that Alex Murphy's sacrifices

1630
01:28:01,781 --> 01:28:04,525
will not have been in vain.

1631
01:28:08,788 --> 01:28:10,998
OHIO SENATOR (voice-over):
Senator Dreyfus is my friend.

1632
01:28:11,083 --> 01:28:14,204
He has been
my mentor and my strength

1633
01:28:14,294 --> 01:28:16,207
in times of difficulty
on this floor.

1634
01:28:16,296 --> 01:28:19,712
But despite all that,
I work for the state of Ohio

1635
01:28:19,799 --> 01:28:23,091
and the safety of its citizens
is my top priority.

1636
01:28:23,220 --> 01:28:25,213
So I vote yes.

1637
01:28:25,347 --> 01:28:27,215
The Dreyfus Act
must be repealed.

1638
01:28:27,307 --> 01:28:30,018
That's us ahead, 39 to 10.

1639
01:28:30,102 --> 01:28:31,560
Yeah, I spoke to
the Senate liaison,

1640
01:28:31,687 --> 01:28:33,396
and it looks like
it's in the bag.

1641
01:28:33,481 --> 01:28:35,896
But we still have to tread
carefully with the politicians.

1642
01:28:38,277 --> 01:28:40,271
We're here live
at DPD headquarters

1643
01:28:40,405 --> 01:28:42,739
where moments ago, Clara Murphy
made a shocking statement.

1644
01:28:42,823 --> 01:28:44,236
POPE:
What the hell?

1645
01:28:44,326 --> 01:28:47,195
Omnicorp has denied me
and my son

1646
01:28:47,287 --> 01:28:48,905
access to Alex for weeks.

1647
01:28:49,040 --> 01:28:52,205
I demand to know why.

1648
01:28:52,292 --> 01:28:54,457
This treatment is inhuman,

1649
01:28:54,586 --> 01:28:57,581
and somebody needs
to be held accountable.

1650
01:28:59,216 --> 01:29:00,958
- CLARA: Thank you.
- Oh, we're fucked.

1651
01:29:01,051 --> 01:29:02,589
No, we only need 12 votes.

1652
01:29:02,719 --> 01:29:03,881
She shouldn't make
much difference.

1653
01:29:03,970 --> 01:29:05,086
Yeah, but what about
after the vote?

1654
01:29:05,221 --> 01:29:06,554
We... I mean,

1655
01:29:06,640 --> 01:29:08,098
those two should not
be allowed contact.

1656
01:29:08,225 --> 01:29:10,889
If-if she starts putting ideas
in his head...

1657
01:29:10,977 --> 01:29:12,139
Bring her in.

1658
01:29:12,271 --> 01:29:13,262
I'll handle the explanation.

1659
01:29:13,397 --> 01:29:14,478
And what about Alex?

1660
01:29:14,606 --> 01:29:16,098
You know, unfortunately,

1661
01:29:16,192 --> 01:29:17,650
we can't just keep him on ice.

1662
01:29:17,735 --> 01:29:19,397
LIZ: The shooting
at the station

1663
01:29:19,486 --> 01:29:20,944
spooked some of the politicians.

1664
01:29:21,072 --> 01:29:23,441
They're our clients;
we have to take care of them.

1665
01:29:23,574 --> 01:29:25,818
They're fine when a machine
is lowering the murder rate,

1666
01:29:25,952 --> 01:29:29,073
but when a man
is investigating city politics,

1667
01:29:29,163 --> 01:29:30,621
they get nervous.

1668
01:29:30,748 --> 01:29:32,786
All right, first off,
it's not a man, okay?

1669
01:29:32,875 --> 01:29:34,493
It's property of Omnicorp.

1670
01:29:34,627 --> 01:29:37,291
And politics are the
least of your concern.

1671
01:29:37,379 --> 01:29:38,997
I mean, this thing
solved its own murder.

1672
01:29:39,132 --> 01:29:40,294
How long till it realizes

1673
01:29:40,425 --> 01:29:41,632
you haven't been
on the level with it?

1674
01:29:41,718 --> 01:29:43,427
POPE: If that happens,
every journalist

1675
01:29:43,511 --> 01:29:45,095
in this country
is dying to speak to him.

1676
01:29:45,180 --> 01:29:47,514
I mean, we-we created a hero.

1677
01:29:48,517 --> 01:29:51,102
What happens
when he opens his mouth?

1678
01:29:53,814 --> 01:29:56,308
What's bigger than a hero?

1679
01:30:06,744 --> 01:30:09,660
A dead hero.

1680
01:30:13,459 --> 01:30:15,452
Get me Dr. Norton.

1681
01:30:24,427 --> 01:30:25,761
What is this, Raymond?

1682
01:30:25,847 --> 01:30:28,090
You have Mattox spying on me

1683
01:30:28,182 --> 01:30:30,472
and now this bullshit
about a "critical condition"?

1684
01:30:30,602 --> 01:30:32,595
You know and I know

1685
01:30:32,687 --> 01:30:33,974
Alex is fine!

1686
01:30:34,105 --> 01:30:35,313
Calm down.

1687
01:30:35,440 --> 01:30:36,476
What... Dennett.

1688
01:30:36,608 --> 01:30:37,770
Your work is so good, I don't...

1689
01:30:37,859 --> 01:30:39,146
Well, now,
this is not about my work!

1690
01:30:39,235 --> 01:30:40,318
You saw the woman on TV!

1691
01:30:40,445 --> 01:30:43,109
This has to stop!

1692
01:30:45,492 --> 01:30:47,404
You're right.

1693
01:30:47,535 --> 01:30:49,154
But let me
ask you something, Dennett.

1694
01:30:49,288 --> 01:30:52,123
What kind of life have we really
given Alex Murphy?

1695
01:30:52,206 --> 01:30:53,825
He's never gonna be
a normal man,

1696
01:30:53,918 --> 01:30:55,705
a father, a husband.

1697
01:30:55,836 --> 01:30:57,999
By the time we put
the other units on the street,

1698
01:30:58,129 --> 01:31:00,464
he's just... Dennett...

1699
01:31:00,549 --> 01:31:01,837
(sighs)

1700
01:31:01,967 --> 01:31:04,553
Let's face it.

1701
01:31:04,679 --> 01:31:07,469
We failed him.

1702
01:31:07,556 --> 01:31:09,220
We failed Alex Murphy.

1703
01:31:09,309 --> 01:31:11,176
But I want you to think
about the bigger picture

1704
01:31:11,268 --> 01:31:13,011
because that's
what we're talking about.

1705
01:31:13,145 --> 01:31:15,639
The work you've done with him
is gonna be studied for decades.

1706
01:31:15,730 --> 01:31:17,849
You've changed
the face of history, Dennett.

1707
01:31:17,983 --> 01:31:21,024
No policeman
is ever going to die

1708
01:31:21,111 --> 01:31:22,353
in the line of duty again

1709
01:31:22,447 --> 01:31:24,781
because of you.

1710
01:31:26,283 --> 01:31:28,277
Think about that.

1711
01:31:35,836 --> 01:31:38,330
I want that family

1712
01:31:38,421 --> 01:31:41,337
taken care of
beyond their wildest dreams.

1713
01:31:41,424 --> 01:31:42,541
We owe them that.

1714
01:31:42,634 --> 01:31:44,091
I agree.

1715
01:31:44,219 --> 01:31:46,429
I want full funding

1716
01:31:46,555 --> 01:31:48,046
for ten years.

1717
01:31:48,139 --> 01:31:50,179
New staff, all my own people.

1718
01:31:50,267 --> 01:31:52,054
Fantastic.

1719
01:31:52,185 --> 01:31:53,598
Deal.

1720
01:32:03,114 --> 01:32:05,073
Hey, what's going on?

1721
01:32:05,199 --> 01:32:06,235
Security's here.

1722
01:32:06,367 --> 01:32:07,574
They're clearing everyone out.

1723
01:32:07,701 --> 01:32:09,239
They're not waking him up.

1724
01:32:09,328 --> 01:32:11,412
Whatever you do,
don't leave him alone.

1725
01:32:11,497 --> 01:32:13,081
What do you mean
they're not waking him up?

1726
01:32:13,165 --> 01:32:15,955
SENATE LEADER:
The voting period has ended.

1727
01:32:16,043 --> 01:32:18,127
The clerks have
tabulated the results.

1728
01:32:18,254 --> 01:32:21,090
The yeas are 63.

1729
01:32:21,216 --> 01:32:22,924
The nays are 22.

1730
01:32:23,050 --> 01:32:25,795
A majority of senators
have voted in the affirmative.

1731
01:32:25,928 --> 01:32:28,548
The Dreyfus Act
has been repealed

1732
01:32:28,723 --> 01:32:29,930
by Congress.

1733
01:32:30,016 --> 01:32:31,976
(applause over TV)

1734
01:32:34,354 --> 01:32:35,937
(phone rings)

1735
01:32:36,022 --> 01:32:38,141
God, you guys are slow,
like a bunch of girls.

1736
01:32:38,275 --> 01:32:39,310
This is Mattox.

1737
01:32:39,442 --> 01:32:41,060
SELLARS:
Dennett's on board.

1738
01:32:41,153 --> 01:32:43,146
It's about time.

1739
01:32:47,326 --> 01:32:49,568
Call it.

1740
01:32:49,661 --> 01:32:51,119
Get it done.

1741
01:32:51,204 --> 01:32:53,197
My pleasure.

1742
01:32:55,626 --> 01:32:57,619
(doorbell rings)

1743
01:33:01,632 --> 01:33:02,873
Mrs. Murphy...

1744
01:33:02,966 --> 01:33:04,504
You can come here
as much as you want.

1745
01:33:04,635 --> 01:33:05,968
You can threaten me.

1746
01:33:06,095 --> 01:33:07,460
You can sue me.
You can take my home.

1747
01:33:07,554 --> 01:33:09,218
But I am not gonna stop
till I see my husband.

1748
01:33:09,348 --> 01:33:10,636
Do you understand that?

1749
01:33:10,767 --> 01:33:14,058
Mr. Sellars would
very much like to see you.

1750
01:33:15,271 --> 01:33:16,808
Is Alex okay?

1751
01:33:16,897 --> 01:33:18,811
He has important information
to share with you.

1752
01:33:18,942 --> 01:33:21,356
Will you accompany me?

1753
01:33:22,528 --> 01:33:24,863
David.

1754
01:33:24,989 --> 01:33:25,980
We gotta go.

1755
01:33:26,115 --> 01:33:27,197
Can you grab your coat?

1756
01:33:27,325 --> 01:33:28,361
(phone rings)

1757
01:33:28,492 --> 01:33:29,859
Hey.

1758
01:33:29,994 --> 01:33:31,361
NORTON: I'm in the elevator,
on my way down.

1759
01:33:31,496 --> 01:33:33,033
I need access to the lab.

1760
01:33:33,164 --> 01:33:34,247
That's insane;
they're still here.

1761
01:33:34,374 --> 01:33:35,786
NORTON:
Distract them.

1762
01:33:35,875 --> 01:33:37,493
Okay.

1763
01:33:39,046 --> 01:33:40,002
I cannot...!

1764
01:33:40,129 --> 01:33:42,169
There's a lady in here
going hysterical.

1765
01:33:42,299 --> 01:33:44,212
She will not let us in;
she's got the code for the door.

1766
01:33:44,343 --> 01:33:45,459
I repeat:
She will not let us in.

1767
01:33:45,552 --> 01:33:46,840
Lady, you need to let us
in there now.

1768
01:33:46,929 --> 01:33:48,341
We have to get in there.

1769
01:33:48,430 --> 01:33:49,968
Are you not understanding
what I'm saying?

1770
01:33:50,057 --> 01:33:51,844
Do you want to be responsible
for the deaths

1771
01:33:51,934 --> 01:33:52,891
of everyone in this building?

1772
01:33:53,018 --> 01:33:54,008
Hey! Stop!

1773
01:33:54,143 --> 01:33:56,137
(panting)

1774
01:33:58,232 --> 01:33:59,189
Don't shoot.

1775
01:33:59,274 --> 01:34:01,644
Step outside.

1776
01:34:07,700 --> 01:34:09,488
Unlock the transmitter!

1777
01:34:09,577 --> 01:34:11,786
KIM:
Transmitter unlocked.

1778
01:34:18,336 --> 01:34:20,706
Send in Mrs. Murphy, please.

1779
01:34:20,839 --> 01:34:22,501
WOMAN (over intercom):
Right away, sir.

1780
01:34:24,550 --> 01:34:26,168
NORTON (voice-over):
Wake him up!

1781
01:34:26,261 --> 01:34:29,587
Alex! Alex!

1782
01:34:29,723 --> 01:34:30,714
Alex, it's Dr. Norton.

1783
01:34:30,807 --> 01:34:32,846
You have to wake up!

1784
01:34:32,934 --> 01:34:34,552
Alex, can you hear me?

1785
01:34:35,770 --> 01:34:37,012
These men are here to kill us.

1786
01:34:37,105 --> 01:34:38,563
They're here to kill us,

1787
01:34:38,650 --> 01:34:40,436
for Christ sakes!

1788
01:34:44,988 --> 01:34:46,902
SELLARS (voice-over):
Mrs. Murphy, last night,

1789
01:34:46,991 --> 01:34:48,778
Alex had a psychotic break.

1790
01:34:48,910 --> 01:34:50,868
He killed an unarmed colleague

1791
01:34:50,952 --> 01:34:53,196
and later suffered a seizure.

1792
01:34:53,289 --> 01:34:55,874
We did everything--

1793
01:34:55,957 --> 01:34:57,746
everything-- we could,

1794
01:34:57,835 --> 01:34:59,121
but the doctors
couldn't save him.

1795
01:35:00,337 --> 01:35:01,922
Very sorry, Mrs. Murphy.

1796
01:35:02,049 --> 01:35:04,040
We're going to be making
the announcement shortly.

1797
01:35:04,132 --> 01:35:06,547
ROBOCOP (voice-over):
You shut me down.

1798
01:35:06,636 --> 01:35:08,253
I was about to get a confession.

1799
01:35:08,387 --> 01:35:11,759
Mattox shut you down.

1800
01:35:11,849 --> 01:35:13,056
I've removed your transmitter,

1801
01:35:13,142 --> 01:35:14,761
so he won't do it again.

1802
01:35:14,895 --> 01:35:17,935
Sellars can't afford
to wake you up.

1803
01:35:18,022 --> 01:35:20,517
He sent these guys
to pull the plug.

1804
01:35:20,609 --> 01:35:22,567
He wants you dead, Alex.

1805
01:35:22,652 --> 01:35:24,270
You understand?

1806
01:35:24,404 --> 01:35:25,817
SELLARS (voice-over):
Sorry. If there's anything

1807
01:35:25,948 --> 01:35:28,112
we can do for you and
David, we'll do it.

1808
01:35:28,200 --> 01:35:30,820
I want nothing from you.

1809
01:35:30,953 --> 01:35:32,490
I understand.

1810
01:35:32,620 --> 01:35:35,035
You stay out of our lives.

1811
01:35:36,249 --> 01:35:37,991
You and your company.

1812
01:35:38,127 --> 01:35:39,994
If that's what
you think is best.

1813
01:35:40,128 --> 01:35:41,837
There's one more thing.

1814
01:35:41,964 --> 01:35:44,174
I think it would be to
the benefit of everyone,

1815
01:35:44,300 --> 01:35:45,540
especially David,

1816
01:35:45,633 --> 01:35:47,968
if we kept
this matter private.

1817
01:35:48,053 --> 01:35:51,015
We don't want to damage
Alex's legacy.

1818
01:35:52,225 --> 01:35:53,968
NORTON (voice-over):
Alex.

1819
01:35:54,102 --> 01:35:55,183
Alex!

1820
01:35:55,310 --> 01:35:56,518
I can fix this!

1821
01:35:56,645 --> 01:35:57,761
You lied to me.

1822
01:35:57,855 --> 01:35:59,643
You lied to my wife.

1823
01:35:59,732 --> 01:36:01,476
You're working for the people
that are trying to kill me.

1824
01:36:01,610 --> 01:36:02,692
You want me to
trust you, Doctor?

1825
01:36:02,819 --> 01:36:04,937
Alex, I can go to the press!

1826
01:36:05,029 --> 01:36:08,320
Alex, I can tell them
the whole story!

1827
01:36:08,407 --> 01:36:11,198
Alex!

1828
01:36:11,327 --> 01:36:14,288
Listen to me, please!

1829
01:36:14,373 --> 01:36:15,614
Alex!

1830
01:36:15,707 --> 01:36:17,700
Alex...!

1831
01:36:26,468 --> 01:36:28,552
(engine roaring)

1832
